cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM 

This paper deals with the problem of localizing digital signs on images, which is a common task in computer vision. The proposed approach uses deep learning based semantic segmentation, which is a popular technique in the field of computer vision and falls under the category of cs.CV. The paper also introduces a new dataset, Barcode-30k, which is likely to be of interest to researchers working on computer vision tasks related to object detection and segmentation, and falls under the category of cs.LG. The paper also proposes a novel dual pyramid structure based segmentation network, which involves the use of advanced techniques such as Prior Pyramid Pooling Module and Pyramid Refine Module, and falls under the categories of cs.AI, cs.IR, and cs.MM.
